    <title>Liberian Refugee Immigration Fairness Act of 2018</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2018-01-03</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2018-01-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-01-17T22:36:31Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Liberian Refugee Immigration Fairness Act of 2018 </strong></p> <p> This bill directs the Department of Homeland Security to adjust to permanent resident status a qualifying Liberian national who: (1) has been continuously present in the United States between November 20, 2014, through the date of status adjustment application; or (2) is the spouse, child, or unmarried son or daughter of such an alien.</p> <p> Adjustment applications must be filed not later than one year after the date of enactment of this bill.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
